  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying American Samoa",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/0_Summary_Graphic.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/as_locator.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/american-samoa/as_locator.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**American Samoa** is a group of islands east of Fiji, located in the Pacific Ocean. Since it is a US overseas territory, for country streak purposes, it is counted as the US."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/image.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/9J2TRoEJL2CfdnZF9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The general landscape consists of **green, tropical** mountains with many palm trees. Small roads are often made of [concrete](https://goo.gl/maps/GENv4jmjUzvkSbp38). Most houses are one storey, and have a simple box design. Plain **metal sheet** roofs are also very common."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Island specific clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/main_island_car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/JsSbHdpLifbJ1Jdt8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "A slightly **rusted black** truck bed can be seen on the main island of Tutuila.",
              "This is the most common car that will be seen as it has the most coverage."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/other_island_car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/Ec2D9s8PzZsWwfkXA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The front of a **silver-grey** truck with side mirrors can be seen on Manu\u2019a and Olosega, which are connected by a bridge.",
              "_See below for more information._"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/other_other_island_car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/89AgZvTc9HJjYqCk8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The front of a similar truck can be seen on the easternmost covered island of Tau. However, the truck will be **glossy black**, with side mirrors visible."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/bride.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/KyriaPF11ZHRuwM47",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The **single-lane** bridge, connecting the islands of Manu\u2019a and Olosega, can be easily recognized by the thin wire guardrail, with the two islands on either side of the bridge."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "guardrail"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/american-samoa/boeing_real_estate.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/mK54EUK79dgWx7qv6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Ofu Airport is small with a **concrete** runway. The Google Car covering it has two **orange straps** on the roof. Many palm trees can also be seen on the other side of the runway."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
